{"text": "Published: Still, the blue-chip index is down 9.1% from its intraday record high on Jan. 26 By The Dow Jones Industrial Average rebounded by 1.4% on Friday, with all but four of 30 companies rising. The gains were led by Nike. The S&P 500 Index was up 1.5%, driven by Mattel. The Dow Jones Industrial Average closed at 24,190.90, producing a decline of 9.1% from its intraday record high of 26,616.71 on Jan. 26. The S&P 500 closed at 2,619.55 and was down 8.8% from its intraday record high of 2,872.87, also on Jan. 26.     Information technology \u2014 last year\u2019s hottest sector \u2014 was strongest on Friday. The best sector this month has been consumer discretionary, with a 2.2% gain, while all other sectors have posted declines. The worst sector of February has been energy, with an 11.3% decline.      Philip van Doorn covers various investment and industry topics.  He has previously worked as a senior analyst at TheStreet.com. He also has experience in community banking and as a credit analyst at the Federal Home Loan Bank of New York. Philip van Doorn covers various investment and industry topics.  He has previously worked as a senior analyst at TheStreet.com. He also has experience in community banking and as a credit analyst at the Federal Home Loan Bank of New York. Join the conversation Copyright \u00a9 2018 MarketWatch, Inc.  All rights reserved. By using this site you agree to the , , and .", "link": "https://www.marketwatch.com/story/dow-jones-industrial-average-rebounds-powered-by-nike-and-microsoft-2018-02-09", "source": "MarketWatch", "author": "Philip van Doorn", "tick": "NVDA", "headline": "Dow Jones Industrial Average rebounds, powered by Nike and Microsoft - MarketWatch"}
