{"text": "Following the market opening Friday, the Dow traded up 0.65 percent to 24,015.69 while the NASDAQ climbed 0.97 percent to 6,842.82. The S&P also rose, gaining 0.86 percent to 2,603.17. Friday morning, the technology shares climbed 1.57 percent. Meanwhile, top gainers in the sector included (NYSE: ), up 18 percent, and (NYSE: ), up 11 percent. In trading on Friday, energy shares fell 0.01 percent. Meanwhile, top losers in the sector included (NYSE: ), down 20 percent, and (NYSE: ) down 6 percent.  (NASDAQ: ) reported better-than-expected earnings for its fourth quarter on Thursday. Nvidia reported fourth quarter-adjusted earnings of $1.72 per share, beating estimates by 56 cents. Sales came in at $2.91 billion, beating estimates by $230 million. The company also issued strong first quarter sales guidance. Nvidia sees Q1 sales of $2.9 billion, plus or minus 2 percent, against estimates of $2.47 billion.  (NASDAQ: ) shares shot up 47 percent to $4.47 after falling 19.74 percent on Thursday. Shares of (NYSE: ) got a boost, shooting up 26 percent to $16.35. Alliance One International reported Q3 earnings of $9.80 per share on revenue of $477 million. (NYSE: ) shares were also up, gaining 23 percent to $8.05 following better-than-expected quarterly profit.  (NASDAQ: ) shares dropped 19 percent to $2.22 after the company reported Q2 results. Shares of (NASDAQ: ) were down 17 percent to $5.40. Miragen Therapeutics priced its 7 million share public offering of common stock at $5.50 per share. (NASDAQ: ) was down, falling around 18 percent to $17.77 after reporting results for the fourth quarter.  In commodity news, oil traded down 1.47 percent to $60.25 while gold traded down 0.08 percent to $1,317.90. Silver traded down 0.34 percent Friday to $16.285, while copper fell 0.89 percent to $3.0545.  European shares were lower today. The eurozone\u2019s STOXX 600 slipped 1.45 percent, the Spanish Ibex Index fell 1.42 percent, while Italy\u2019s FTSE MIB Index dropped 1.32 percent. Meanwhile the German DAX dropped 1.52 percent, and the French CAC 40 fell 1.44 percent while U.K. shares fell 0.89 percent. U.S. wholesale inventories rose 0.40 percent for December, versus economists\u2019 expectations for a 0.20 percent growth. The Baker Hughes North American rig count report for the latest week is schedule for release at 1:00 p.m. ET.      ", "link": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/18/02/11168080/mid-morning-market-update-markets-open-higher-nvidia-earnings-beat-estimates?utm_campaign=partner_feed&utm_source=marketwatch.com&utm_medium=web_click&utm_content=ticker_page", "source": "MarketWatch", "author": null, "tick": "NVDA", "headline": "Mid-Morning Market Update: Markets Open Higher; NVIDIA Earnings Beat Estimates | Benzinga"}
